Simulation can be elegant, fast, and should be accessible to more people.
Headquarters Regions: San Francisco Bay Area, Silicon Valley, West Coast
Full Description: Simulation can be elegant, fast, and should be accessible to more people. The days of $50K for an entry level license package (that doesn't fully take advantage of GPU computing!) are numbered – there are untapped markets beyond big-budget corporations. A singular well-conceived architecture cannot only be applied to numerous different industries, but a small core code-base has the virtue of easier maintainability/optimization - and since the concepts are universal, it is easier to learn and implement. The face of computer-aided engineering is changing. Winning architectures will be collaborative 3D environments (with Virtual Reality and other tech) with a more seamless workflow/experience.    We think the timing is perfect to introduce a disruptive, unified, high-performance architecture that could eventually become the standard in engineering systems design, optimization and analysis...and other industries. Someday, simulation will be run realtime for safety/operations analysis in vehicles and/or used for entertainment purposes. Applications are unbounded.
